{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 3: collection.liquid","content":"<html><head></head><body><p><img src=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/part03_banner.png\" alt=\"part03_banner\" width=\"800\" height=\"186\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3138\"></p>\n<p>The collection page is where you see a handful of products in a collection at once. This part is actually going to be a breeze thanks to all the hard work we did in Part 2. &#x1F642;</p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s rock and/or roll!</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Navigate to the Frontpage collection</h2>\n<p>Navigate to the default &#x201C;Frontpage&#x201D; collection in your shop. To do this, you can either plug in <em>your-store-name.myshopify.com/collections/frontpage</em> into the URL bar of your browser, or click the &#x201C;View in your store&#x201D; link in the Frontpage collection in the admin (Figure 3.1).</p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 35.7609710550887%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3176\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"viewing your collection\" title src=\"/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/a111b/viewing-your-collection.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/aca85/viewing-your-collection.jpg 163w,\n/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/0954f/viewing-your-collection.jpg 325w,\n/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/a111b/viewing-your-collection.jpg 650w,\n/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/ce471/viewing-your-collection.jpg 975w,\n/static/1128d3e009563805a7e8d43b1df928f5/8e162/viewing-your-collection.jpg 1071w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 3.1: This link will take you to the collection on the storefront.</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Add the collection description</h2>\n<p>We&#x2019;ll start off by outputting the collection&#x2019;s description, which can be inserted through the admin (see Fig 3.1). Go ahead and enter a nice little description for your Frontpage collection.</p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 36.074766355140184%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3142\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"collection desc\" title src=\"/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/a111b/collection-desc.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/aca85/collection-desc.jpg 163w,\n/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/0954f/collection-desc.jpg 325w,\n/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/a111b/collection-desc.jpg 650w,\n/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/ce471/collection-desc.jpg 975w,\n/static/30d8c59a7c75d84a505e431188052099/47651/collection-desc.jpg 1070w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Fig 3.2: the collection description can be inserted through the collection&#x2019;s page in the Admin.</div>\n<p>Open collection.liquid. Remove the &#x201C;This is my collection page!&#x201D; text, and insert the code below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\"><div class=\"clearfix\">\n  <h2>{{ collection.title }}</h2>\n  <div class=\"collection-desc rte\">\n    {{ collection.description }}\n  </div>\n</div></span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You will now see the collection description being output on your collection template.</p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.24242424242425%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3145\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"collection description output\" title src=\"/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/a111b/collection-description-output.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/aca85/collection-description-output.jpg 163w,\n/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/0954f/collection-description-output.jpg 325w,\n/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/a111b/collection-description-output.jpg 650w,\n/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/ce471/collection-description-output.jpg 975w,\n/static/97a47afea2a50fd2794f9f89a43f996f/c9b5c/collection-description-output.jpg 990w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></p>\n<h3>Why don&#x2019;t I need to use {% assign %}, like in Part 2?</h3>\n<p>We do not need an assign here because when you&#x2019;re on a collection template, you already know which collection you&#x2019;re viewing. You were taken to the collection template by clicking on a collection link, so the template already knows which collection to load. In our case, the template is loading the Frontpage collection.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Output the products in the collection</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s go ahead and output the products of the collection. We can simply use the product-loop.liquid snippet that we made in Part 2.</p>\n<p>Add the code in red below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<div class=\"clearfix\">\n  <h2>{{ collection.title }}</h2>\n  <div class=\"collection-desc rte\">\n    {{ collection.description }}\n  </div>\n  <span style=\"color:red;\">{% for product in collection.products %}\n    {% include &apos;product-loop&apos; %}\n  {% endfor %}</span>\n</div>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You should now see the products of the Frontpage collection being output &#x1F642;</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Paginate the products in the collection</h2>\n<p>One thing that we need to do with the collection template is to paginate. Pagination is useful for when you only want to show a set amount of products per collection page. It&#x2019;s also required for when you have more than 50 products, because there is a limit of 50 products that can be output per product page. Pagination lets you get around that limit.</p>\n<p>Now in our case we only have 9 products, but let&#x2019;s go ahead paginate our collection template by 8. Enter the code in red below below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% paginate collection.products by 8 %}</span>\n\n<div class=\"clearfix\">\n  <h2>{{ collection.title }}</h2>\n  <div class=\"collection-desc rte\">\n    {{ collection.description }}\n  </div>\n  {% for product in collection.products %}\n    {% include &apos;product-loop&apos; %}\n  {% endfor %}\n</div>\n\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if paginate.pages &gt; 1 %}\n<div class=\"pagination\">\n  {{ paginate | default_pagination }}\n</div>\n{% endif %}\n\n{% endpaginate %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You&#x2019;ll now see that 8 of the 9 products in the Frontpage collection are shown. You&#x2019;ll also see a set of links at the bottom to go the different pages.</p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 88.00792864222002%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3178\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"pagination\" title src=\"/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/a111b/pagination.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/aca85/pagination.jpg 163w,\n/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/0954f/pagination.jpg 325w,\n/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/a111b/pagination.jpg 650w,\n/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/ce471/pagination.jpg 975w,\n/static/c94c6b876627631fd01fde640c63ef7c/0110e/pagination.jpg 1009w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 3.3: Pagination at work</div>\n<p>If you click on the &#x201C;2&#x201D; link, you will be taken to the second page, where you&#x2019;ll see the ninth product.</p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.66531440162272%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-3179\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"forever alone\" title src=\"/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/a111b/forever-alone.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/aca85/forever-alone.jpg 163w,\n/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/0954f/forever-alone.jpg 325w,\n/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/a111b/forever-alone.jpg 650w,\n/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/ce471/forever-alone.jpg 975w,\n/static/fe1d36dc658ec54cd0c68b1b3a49ee19/33529/forever-alone.jpg 986w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 3.4: This product is now forever alone, not unlike the author of this tutorial</div>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s add some CSS for the pagination links. Open style.css, and at the bottom of the file add the following CSS:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n/**** collection.liquid ****/\n\n.pagination{text-align:center; border-top:1px solid #ccc; padding-top: 30px; margin-top: 30px;}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>That&#x2019;s it for now!</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a></p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-3"}}